From 752c13efc11d9fae8924aacf45922d3a1a337bfe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcos <marcosbrendonaz@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 18:30:43 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] feat: anti-webdriver detection - hide automation from all
 detection methods

- navigator.webdriver always returns false (navigator.cc)
- ChromeDriver $cdc_ variables replaced with random names (devtools_client_impl.cc)
- CDP setAutomationOverride silently ignored (inspector_emulation_agent.cc)
- "Chrome is being controlled" infobar disabled (infobar_utils.cc)
- --enable-automation flag not propagated to renderer (render_process_host_impl.cc)

Selenium/Playwright/Puppeteer automation is now completely invisible.
Tested: dual Selenium profiles with different fingerprints simultaneously.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
